        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 5:12PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bridgeport. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Bridgeport Reservoir, Junction U.S 395 And CA 270 (Bodie
Rd), Buckeye Campground, and Bridgeport-Bryant Field Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
